div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">This plugin makes it easy to define redirects. It is useful, because I replaced the previous website with an entirely new one. This way, people will find the information, even if they use outdated links.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Redirect Sub Category to Post</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				By <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/titusraj\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4fd5263efeb073f02c47c742d71a3268?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/4fd5263efeb073f02c47c742d71a3268?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/titusraj\" class=\"reviewer-name\">titusraj</a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 18, 2019</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">After the latest wordpress update, I was getting redirect errors for google indexed links for subcategories to post, tried everything, then found this plugin, worked straight away. Wished I had found it 8 hours earlier.</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Awesome</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div clas